==English==

===Etymology===
Named for [[w:Jean-Maurice-Émile Baudot|Jean-Maurice-Émile Baudot (1845-1903)]].

===Noun===
'''baud''', sometimes seen capitalized.

# A rate defined as the number of signaling events per second in a data transmission.
# (''colloquial'') Synonym for bps (bits per second), regardless of how many signaling events are necessary to signal each bit.